      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p><strong>Last updated: October 1, 2023</strong></p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how the Notion Journal Digest Integration
        (referred to as "Integration", "we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and
        shares your information when you use our Integration with Notion to
        provide you with weekly digests of your journal entries.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

      <strong>a. Journal Data:</strong>
      <p>
        We access your journal entries stored in Notion for the sole purpose of
        generating weekly digests. This includes all text, images, links, and
        other content you may have included in your journal entries.
      </p>

      <strong>b. Notion Account Information:</strong>
      <p>
        We retrieve your Notion account name and email address to communicate
        with you and for authentication purposes.
      </p>

      <strong>c. Device and Usage Data:</strong>
      <p>
        We collect information about the devices you use to access our
        Integration, including IP addresses, device type, operating system, and
        other related technical information. We also track actions taken within
        the Integration for improving the functionality and user experience.
      </p>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>

      <strong>a. Providing the Service:</strong>
      <p>
        We process your journal entries to create and deliver the weekly digests
        to you.
      </p>

      <strong>b. Communication:</strong>
      <p>
        We use your email address to send you service-related communications.
      </p>

      <strong>c. Improvement:</strong>
      <p>
        We use device and usage data to improve our Integration, troubleshoot
        issues, and optimize the user experience.
      </p>

      <strong>d. Security:</strong>
      <p>
        To ensure the safety of your information, we use the data for security
        monitoring and incident response.
      </p>

      <h2>3. How We Share Your Information</h2>

      <p>
        We commit to preserving the confidentiality of your journal entries. We
        do not share, sell, or disclose your journal content or personal
        information with third parties, except in the following situations:
      </p>

      <strong>a. Legal Requirements:</strong>
      <p>
        We may disclose your information when required by law, subpoena, or if
        we believe it's necessary to protect our rights or the safety of others.
      </p>

      <strong>b. Business Transfers:</strong>
      <p>
        If we undergo a business merger, acquisition, or asset sale, your
        information may be transferred as part of that transaction.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Data Security</h2>

      <p>
        We take your privacy seriously. We use industry-standard encryption
        techniques to safeguard your information. It is important to us that
        your data remains secure and confidential at all times.
      </p>
